In Lab 4, I performed a full data‑preprocessing workflow on the Online Retail dataset.
I began by identifying data quality issues such as missing values and inconsistencies,
then applied an appropriate missing‑value strategy to clean the dataset. Outliers were
detected and handled using the IQR method to improve data reliability. Next, I normalized
the numerical features using both Min‑Max scaling and Z‑score standardization to ensure 
consistent feature ranges. Finally, I evaluated feature correlation and applied PCA for 
  demonstration, showing that Quantity and UnitPrice were uncorrelated and PCA did not 
significantly reduce dimensionality.
